revision.text:
'''Adelphogamy''' is a form of sexual partnership between [[sibling]] [[eukaryote]]s, for example in some species of [[fungus|fungi]], [[flowering plant]]s or [[ant]]s, or in [[human]]s. In sociology, the term ''adelphogamy'' may also refer to [[fraternal polyandry]] or to a relationship between a [[brother]] and [[sister]].<ref>Rudmin, Floyd Webster. "Cross-cultural correlates of the ownership of private property: A look from another data base." Anthropologica (1992): 71-88.</ref>

